### 4. Key Update for OSCORE (KUDOS)
* **Presenter:** Rikard Höglund
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-core-oscore-key-update](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-core-oscore-key-update)
* **Slides:** [Slides KUDOS CoRE IETF 126](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-core-slides-kudos-core-ietf-126-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Rikard Höglund outlined updates in version 14, including the removal of a redundant YANG model for SCHC and the addition of an implementation status section.
  * Successful hackathon interoperability tests were performed in forward secrecy mode between Java (Californium) and C (uOSCORE/uEDHOC) implementations. 
  * Consecutive execution tests revealed a minor bug where the replay window failed to reset on context re-derivation, which the authors plan to resolve.
  * Lessons learned include clarifying the sorting mechanism to use "short lex order" and prefixing vector data types with their lengths per the TLS RFC.
  * Christian Amsüss noted via chat that he has editorial suggestions regarding renaming the "x byte."

